author: @AcePlaysTCGs
text: If there ever was a movie that called for a new look every 20 years or so, it's probably this one. I'm sure, based on this trailer, the dialogue won't be much different, but some of the approaches will be very different. We can already tell there will be a tik tok/internet/influencer presence that the story would definitely benefit from including. 2004 predates YouTube. Just because this could be a Mean Girls for the next generation doesn't mean it has to unseat the 2004 one as a classic. If they remade Breakfast Club, it would include a lot of advanced technology, but the more things change, the more they stay the same. High school is all about finding yourself in a world where fitting in is the name of the game and I have faith in this iteration. It's got a lot of the same people behind it both on camera and in production. It's going to be just as fun as the original with a few new generational tweaks. Sign me up.
